    "Although a great number of researchers is involved in research activities, the (great) contributions result from only a small part of their shoulders.",
    "Price's law (Price, 1963) implies that only about 25% of researchers are responsible for about 75% of publications (van Raan, 2019).",
    "One important reason for the unequal distribution among the shoulders might be the high number of temporary researchers in the system.",
    "Only a small part of researchers spend their full career in science (Milojevic et al., 2018).",
    "Amara et al. (2015) did not only differentiate researchers with respect to their publication output performance, but also with respect to their citation impact performance."
